parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
often at low speeds
and may be accompanied by the illumination of the check engine warning light. The vehicle may also experience difficulty starting or may not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to stall or shut off, leading to a loss of power and control.

often accompanied by the illumination of the check engine warning light. The vehicle may also experience difficulty starting or may not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage and potentially causing a fire.
symptoms: The engine overheats
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power and performance. The check engine warning light may also illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can cause engine damage and potentially lead to engine failure.

and the engine may experience damage or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dipstick can cause the engine to overheat and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: The dipstick breaks or becomes stuck
making it difficult to check the oil level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.

the engine stalls

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly repair or replace the Takata airbag inflators can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Failure to receive recall notification
inability to schedule repair
parts distribution disconnect
refusal to repair without assuming responsibility for damage
airbag warning light illumination
and airbag deployment failure.
